<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1349">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/123.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Ambassador <persName type="to">Willard</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your January 14. Appropriate telegraphic instructions have been sent
                                to Consuls in Chihuahua. Other consular officers will be suitably
                                instructed to facilitate Mr. Cardenas’s missions at other points he
                                may visit.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>